ee 1976 was an amazing vintage year on the Rhine and Moselle—the Pt Lae happy result of much sunshine and perfect weather. As a result, the ee ‘Spatlesen’ are as rich and fruity as the ‘Auslesen’ of a normal year— ee the ‘Auslesen’ are as overwhelming as ‘Beerenauslesen’—and the

‘Beerenauslesen’ achieved the richness and glory of ‘Trockenbeeren- auslesen’ of less exalted years.

For lovers of German wines, this is an especially blessed time to be

alive. The great 1975 vintage was immediately followed by the even greater 1976 vintage—bringing us a double harvest of wines of excep- tional richness, depth, flavor and longevity. Wines that are ‘historic’ by anyone's definition of the term. Now the lovely 1977s have begun to reach us; lighter, drier, simpler, less costly—but utterly delightful.
